MediaWiki Google Search extension v0.1

Made by Pierre Mavro <pierre@mavro.fr>
Licenced under GPL v2

= Minimum requirements =

* MediaWiki 1.16+ (not tested <1.16)

= Installation instructions =

* Download the latest version of Google Search from :
** The primary link : http://www.mediawiki.org/wiki/Extension:GoogleSearch
** Alternate link : http://git.deimos.fr/gitweb/?p=mediawiki_extensions.git;a=snapshot;h=HEAD;sf=tgz
** Download with git : git clone git://git.deimos.fr/git/mediawiki_extensions.git

* Uncompress it in your extensions directory (ex. /var/www/mediawiki/extensions).

* Edit your LocalSettings.conf and add those lines :

# Google Search
require_once( "$IP/extensions/GoogleSearch/GoogleSearch.php" );

* Create an account and get the code from Google Co-op (CSE) / Google Adsense to replace in GoogleSearch.class.php
  in the $bar['googleSearch'] value. It should looks like this :
  $bar['googleSearch'] = "<form action=\"http://www.google.fr/cse\" id=\"cse-search-box\">
  <div>
    <input type=\"hidden\" name=\"cx\" value=\"partner-pub-YOUR_CODE_HERE\" />
    <input type=\"hidden\" name=\"ie\" value=\"UTF-8\" />
    <input type=\"text\" name=\"q\" size=\"15\" />
    <input type=\"submit\" name=\"sa\" value=\"" .wfMsg('Search'). "\" />
  </div>
</form>";


* That's all, now you can refresh your wiki and see the Google Search in your sidebar

* Do not hesitate to contact me if you have some questions

